    <bioghist>Clergyman from Corunna, Michigan, minister of the Methodist Protestant Church, Allmont Circuit. In 1868 he transferred to the Methodist Episcopal Church, Detroit Conference, by 1910 serving a church in Marion Township, Livingston County, Michigan.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Diaries containing descriptions of his travels, reflections on the Bible, records of sermons preached and letters sent and received; also a membership record of the Allmont Circuit, 1861-1862, a record of marriages solemnized, 1862-1879, letters to his niece (1910-1911), including family news and reminiscences of his boyhood on a farm near Holly, Michigan, in the 1840's and 1850's, and a photograph.</scopecontent>
